Interface Wall<O>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - Object to be protected.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    WalAtmIntArr, WalAtmLongArr, WalAtmRef, WalAtmRefArr, WalAtmRefArrStrict, WalAtmStampRef, WalDir, WalDoubleEps, WalFile, WalFloatEps, WalNaturalInt, WalNegativeDouble, WalNegativeFloat, WalNegativeInt, WalNegativeLong, WalNegativeShort, WalNotEmptyCollection, WalNotEmptyDeque, WalNotEmptyIterable, WalNotEmptyList, WalNotEmptyMap, WalNotEmptyNavigableMap, WalNotEmptyQueue, WalNotEmptySet, WalNotEmptySortedMap, WalNotEmptySortedSet, WalNotEmptyStr, WalNotNull, WalNotZeroInt, WalNotZeroLong, WalNotZeroShort, WalPositiveDouble, WalPositiveFloat, WalPositiveInt, WalPositiveLong, WalPositiveShort

    public interface Wall<O>
    Object protection. obj is object to be protected. objName is the name of obj. If objName is null, then specified by implementation. objName used for exception message. Pay attention: this logic must be implemented in every implementation.
